  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA106-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu (ET: piriviṭai) paruva varaviṉkaṇ paṇṭu nikaḻntatōr kuṟippuṇarnta talaiva[ḷ] (ET: uḷḷiya talaimakaṉ) ataṉaik kaṇṭu tāṅkakillāṉāy mīḷkiṉṟāṉ tērp pākaṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what he who was returning said to the charioteer, being one who could not endure that ‒ SHE who had understood [his] intention ‒ which occurred before when the season was coming.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA106">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            aṟitalu maṟitiyō pāka peruṅkaṭa</l>
<l>            leṟitirai koḻīiya vekkar veṟikoḷa</l>
<l>            vāṭuvari yalava ṉōṭuvayi ṉāṟṟā</l>
<l>            tacaiyuḷ ḷoḻinta vacaitīr kuṟumakaṭ</l>
<l>            kuyaviṉeṉ ceṉṟiyā ṉuṇṇō vuraippa </l>
<l>            maṟumoḻi peyartta lāṟṟā ṇaṟumalar</l>
<l>            ñāḻa lañciṉait tāḻiṇar koḻuti</l>
<l>            muṟitimirn tutirtta kaiya</l>
<l>            ḷaṟivaña ruṟuvi yāymaṭa nilaiyē.</l>
    </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Do you have any knowledge at all<note place="foot">Do we have to understand <term xml:lang="ta">aṟitalum aṟitiyō</term> as a figura etymologica with indefinite marker? For a parallel for the intensifying nuance see KT 276.4.</note>, charioteer?</l>
<l rend="indent2">– of the state of choice innocence of her who has the grief of knowledge,</l>
<l rend="indent2">she with a hand that rubbed [and] dropped a shoot,</l>
<l rend="indent2">picking at the trailing clusters on the pretty Ñāḻal branches</l>
<l rend="indent2">with fragrant blossoms, she who is unable to repel the word of refusal,</l>
<l rend="indent">when I talk of the inner pain, going as one who suffered(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uyaviṉeṉ</term>: how to account here for the syntax? Is this perhaps not to be analysed as a finite form, but as an appellative noun to <term xml:lang="ta">uyavu</term> "suffering"?</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">for the faultless little woman who stayed behind with a shaken mind,</l>
<l rend="indent2">without strength(?) at the place of running after the lined crabs in play(?),</l>
<l rend="indent3">when they are taken by frenzy on the dune enriched by the dashing</l>
<l rend="indent4">waves of the great sea.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
